Our Tactical 3-D Head Targets, with a vinyl exterior shell over a styrofoam core, a plastic bottom, and a hole in the bottom to mount to a post or PVC pipe, are perfect for your shooting needs! title: For Sale/Trade:  EOTECH 512 HOLOGRAPHIC SIGHT FOR AR-15 STYLE RIFLE
postcontent:
EOTECH HOLOGRAPHIC WEAPON SIGHT FOR AR-15 STYLE RIFLE

This is an older model of EOTECH sight and I don't have the original box or remember with certainty what was the actual model number but I believe it is a model 512.

What follows is a description of the unit from experience and memory only.

The holographic sight image displays a very small MOA red dot sight in the center of a round halo ring.
Sight brightness is adjustable for all ambient lighting conditions. Very bright to very dim as needed.
Perfect for a CQB rifle. (Close Quarters Battle)
I'm offering it for sale because I sold the rifle it was attached to and I really don't need it on a different rifle.

There is full size glass aperture to look through which is designed to operate using both eyes open so that you can acquire the target very quickly.
What I like about this model is that it is very short and lightweight because it is powered by short N size photo batteries. (Two Energizer E90 N)

A word on battery life:
Originally, EOTECH sights got a bad reputation for batteries not lasting very long. 
I bought this sight brand new, always left the sight with batteries installed and eventually discovered that the batteries would go dead after a few weeks of the rifle just sitting in the safe.
I took the sight back to the store and they sent it to EOTECH for "repair".
After this sight came back, the battery life while sitting in the safe doing nothing was greatly improved, lasting a number of months.
I can't provide you an exact battery life while the unit sits in the safe but it is now at least 3 or 4 months. But by around 8 months, you can expect the batteries to be dead.
So, the sight is designed for combat, its designed to be used and the operator is expected to put fresh batteries in it as needed. It's not designed to sit in a safe for 8 months at a time.

There are two arrow buttons on the back of the unit, facing the shooter. [DOWN]    [UP]
The UP arrow turns on the unit.  
Once the unit is on, keep pushing the up arrow to increase the brightness of the holographic sight.
The down arrow dims the holographic sight the more you push it. 
Push both buttons at the same time to turn off the unit.

The sight is in mint condition because it sat in the safe for its whole life and only went to the range long enough to sight in the rifle it was attached to.
I also bought a stretchy cover for the sight which feels like it is made from wet suit material.
The sight easilly bolts on to any picatiney rail system using an allen wrench.
Easy adjustments for elevation and windage.

New EOTECH 512's (are no longer made but are still available) go from $375.00-$475 depending on where you shop.
Asking $325.00

title: For Sale:  Accurized browning Abolt with boss-300 win mag
postcontent:
I have a Browning A-bolt in 300 win mag with the BOSS system for Sale. This gun has a couple knicks from being hunted with but has only been shot 27 times. This is a sub moa gun shooting horandy 180 grain loads at 3130 fps. This gun has been accurized by hill country firearms. I hate to sell but I need the cash. I am asking 750OBO and this will include 100 hornady once shot brass I have bought. I will ship but prefer Face to Face. Here is some information on the BOSS system.



What is the BOSS? 
Browning's Ballistic Optimizing Shooting System (BOSS) is a patented breakthrough in rifle accuracy. When any rifle is fired, the barrel goes through a series of vibrations as the bullet leaves the muzzle. The variations of these vibrations greatly affect the accuracy of the rifle. Controlling these vibrations will greatly control the accuracy of the rifle. Browning's BOSS allows you to control the vibrations of your barrel so you can shoot groups you didn't think possible.

How the BOSS works. 
The BOSS simply tunes the vibrations of your barrel. This allows the bullet to leave the barrel the split second it is stationary. Your BOSS manual has a list of settings for each caliber and bullet weight. Adjusting your BOSS to these "Sweet Spot" settings allows you to find the instant your barrel is stationary. The result is accuracy never achieved before by an out-of-the-box rifle.
